---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../components/system/PageShell.astro';
import Badge from '../../components/system/Badge.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <PageShell class="capabilities-shell">
    <header class="page-header"><Badge tone="accent">Capabilities</Badge><h1>Engineering depth with a security habit.</h1><p class="intro">The useful version of my skill set is not a list of impressive words. It is the ability to move from a financial workflow or application boundary down to the code, identity, and state that make it work.</p></header>
    <div class="capability-list">
      <article><span class="number">01</span><div><h2>Software and systems</h2><p>Python, TypeScript, C++, APIs, automation, local tooling, system behavior, and the engineering decisions that make software maintainable.</p></div></article>
      <article><span class="number">02</span><div><h2>Application security</h2><p>Authentication, authorization, business logic, API abuse paths, state manipulation, IDOR, SSRF, and the gaps that appear between features.</p></div></article>
      <article><span class="number">03</span><div><h2>Fintech and finance systems</h2><p>Transactions, account state, limits, ledgers, roles, sessions, and the trust boundaries that matter when software handles money.</p></div></article>
      <article><span class="number">04</span><div><h2>Offensive research</h2><p>Windows internals, C/C++ research, malware analysis, evasion concepts, cloud identity, and controlled exploit development for authorized work.</p></div></article>
      <article><span class="number">05</span><div><h2>Writing and mentorship</h2><p>Turning technical findings into clear notes, useful remediation, and practical learning for engineers who want to understand the system beneath the tool.</p></div></article>
    </div>
  </PageShell>
</Layout>

<style>
  .capabilities-shell { max-width: 980px; }
  .page-header { max-width: 780px; padding: 1.5rem 0 3rem; }
  h1 { margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text); font-size: clamp(2.3rem, 10vw, 5rem); line-height: 1; letter-spacing: 0; }
  .intro, article p { margin-top: 1rem; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.96rem; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.8; }
  .capability-list { border-top: 1px solid var(--border-muted); }
  article { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2rem 1fr; gap: 0.8rem; padding: 1.25rem 0 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-muted); }
  .number { color: var(--accent); font: 0.6rem 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
  h2 { color: var(--text); font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: 0; }
  article p { max-width: 680px; font-size: 0.88rem; }
  @media (min-width: 700px) { .page-header { padding-top: 4rem; padding-bottom: 5rem; } article { grid-template-columns: 150px minmax(0, 680px); gap: 2rem; padding: 1.5rem 0 2rem; } }
</style>
